<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Patriarch on 01-20-2000 02:17 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hehe agian some nagging with Questions.

First for the magic system. Will there be only battle spells or do the magic have a wider range. As far as you said there is a enchanting spell and learning teleport wouldn't be the worst idea or at least have the scroll  :). But I am thinking about other manipulative spells like levitate, flying, telekinesis. locking doors or breathing in water. 
If they are it would be great if they work everywhere and with every object. Its one of the things I don't like in the realms of arcania games, lots of spells you actually never need or didn't work properly. At one point you had to light a torch with fire kit also I had to mages capable of casting a burn spell  :(.
Concerning use of these spells, levitate for example is one of my favorites in p&p avoiding traps, I mean those nasty things going of when you step on them. 
Brings me to the next point traps. Will there be any, and when there are some how can you avoid them. With a Skill ? If yes how the skill works, do one have to turn it on like in BG, or does it work, maybe with another skill like 6th sense automaticly, let the character warn you. Something like : I have a bad feeling about this.     
Will it be possible to run/jump into safety when you trigger a trap, or will one be hit in every case ?
If you detect a trap will it be possible to trigger it from a safe place, with a pole/long weapon or something like that?

Coming to the last point. 
Will there be items like ropes, tools and ordinary stuff you can use ? For example tankards, buckets to catch some water to stop a fire. Just thinking about preparing a hideout in a dungeon, put out some torches and attack the monsters from the shadows or just remove a torch from the wall to have light in a dark area. Hmm doing this could be tricky to programm light and shadows, so I think one can't do this, but it still would be great.
Just in the case you have planned or already implemented a realistic journey mode, with all the equipment needed to do so. Tents, spare weapons, food, water etc. please add a horse or something like that to carry the whole stuff. 



------------------
never trust a smiling Dragon

Patriarch


</TEXTAREA>
